<br>
If any guild can kill a god by themselves, by no means does anyone have any right to tell them what to do with that loot.  If CT was up 10x in a row, killed 10x in a row by non bb guilds WITH 0 assistance and 10x in a row they were given to keg, so be it.  <br>
<br>
The problem i saw was a guild that has (at least no one will answer yes or no, so i assume no) never killed ct completely by themselves, therefore chances are they would not have kiled ct w/o 6 vetran keg members - which would have lead to mfh bb'ing - hence rotation.<br>
<br>
Same rules would apply to trades (for the less loved ~.~ guilds).  if we make a trade to loot, we stay out of zone.  If ct is killed alone, we come in and get the loot.<br>
<br>
And if the items were obtained soley by non-bb killing, then they would not fit in to the rotation of bb.<br>
<br>
Again, i dont think keg did anything wrong - i think the rules simply need modification. <p><P align=center>
