he FFA crap already?  It's not going to happen.  We'll find a way to work it out so as to be as fair as possible across the board, kk??<br>
<br>
I have to agree with Vincecross on this.  No one should be able to tell me that I cannot go to the Planes with United Necros, INC., just because I am in an Epic guild (let's cease calling these guilds/alliances BB...the term makes me cringe).<br>
<br>
Perhaps we can compromise on this and say that rather than 6 invites from Epic, only 3 are allowed.  (I know, this is getting complicated.)  If the guild in the plane does decide to give the Epic loot to someone in an Epic guild/alliance, that is their option.  If that someone is not a part of the invites, they wait outside until the god is being taken down.<br>
<br>
NOTE:  Epic's invited into the plane to assist in clearing and/or taking down the god are allowed as many peeps as they feel are necessary to accomplish the deed.<br>
<br>
Someone have a better idea?<br>
<br>
Other than that, I like the idea of Epic's rotating weeks rather than sitting and waiting for weeks on in to be called in.  It lets the peeps sorta choose who they will call in if needed; however, we may run into instances where the Epic will be called in more than once during their week on server crashes/resets.<br>
<br>
Milambus' idea on Epic removing themselves form the Epic rotation is a good one and something that should be incorporated into our current rules (if nothing else comes out of this).<br>
<br>
I'm rather disappointed in the lack of Epic guild/alliance input on this thread.  This is, after all, something that is for them, and needs to be something that they can agree with.  Perhaps a meeting between these folks should be set up so that they can discuss it amongst themselves and present what they would like to see.<br>
