<br>
It's still a hard call.  By removing the 'bb' element from a non-epic guild raid, you prove, beyond the shadow of a doubt that bb was not required, thus freeing yourselves from any cross server speculation.  This would offer no room for suspicion / cross examination from anyone on the server.  <br>
<br>
It would leave the naysayers without material to gripe, and would still allow for friendly gifts / negotiated trades to take place in game, without reprocussions.<br>
<br>
It would also shed light on exactly how needed bb is.  I hear that bb is virtually obsolete - maybe it is.  Honestly i dont know how needed it it.  This would prove interesting to me, at the very least.<br>
<br>
It seem regulated on the surface, but isnt that exactly what the callendar is? Regulation, to ensure unbiassed sharing of planar loot to server sanctioned entities, regardless of social standing in the community?  I'd like to take this model and apply it to epic loot.<br>
<br>
Don't think of the suggestion as a was to thwart keg, think of it as a way to evenly distribute the epic stuff amongst the 6 epic guilds.<br>
